			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">Soapless soaps; Synthetic cleaning compounds; Non-soapy cleaning agent</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">Soapless soaps; Synthetic cleaning compounds; Non-soapy cleaning agent</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Other materials</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Detergent is a surfactant or a mixture of surfactants with cleansing properties when in dilute solutions. Conventionally, detergent is used to mean synthetic cleaning compounds as opposed to soap. They are chemically different from soaps but are able to emulsify oils, hold dirt in suspension, and act as wetting agents. Detergents are not prepared from fats and oils, are not inactivated by hard water, and have wetting-agent and emulsifying-agent properties. They are effective even in hard or saltwater, unlike soaps, because they do not develop scum.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">洗涤剂是一种表面活性剂或表面活性剂混合物，在稀释溶液中具有清洁特性。通常，洗涤剂指的是合成清洁化合物，而不是肥皂。它们与肥皂的化学性质不同，但能乳化油，使污垢悬浮，并起到润湿剂的作用。洗涤剂不是由油脂制备的，不会被硬水灭活，具有润湿剂和乳化剂的特性。它们与肥皂不同，即使在硬水或盐水中也有效，因为它们不会产生浮渣。</common:generalComment>
